									<title>MOD Authors Convention, 30 June 2007</title>
									<description>&lt;span style="font-size: 175%; line-height: 116%;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: indigo"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: bold"&gt;MOD Authors Convention&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;With the &lt;a href="http&#58;//www&#46;phpbb&#46;com/community/viewtopic&#46;php?f=14&amp;t=543015" class="postlink"&gt;release of phpBB 3.0.0RC1&lt;/a&gt; and subsequent &lt;a href="http&#58;//www&#46;phpbb&#46;com/community/viewtopic&#46;php?f=70&amp;t=543793" class="postlink"&gt;opening of the phpBB3 MODs section&lt;/a&gt;, the phpBB MOD team would like to invite MOD authors to the &lt;span style="font-weight: bold"&gt;MOD Authors Convention&lt;/span&gt;. The convention will be hosted in the #phpbb-mod IRC channel all day on June 30, 2007. The convention will go on all day. The topics of discussion will be anything MODding-related, specifically phpBB3-related MODding. Have you been meaning to start MODding? Do you have some questions about phpBB3 MODding that you would like cleared up? If so, now is the time to come and find out! Many members of the &lt;a href="http&#58;//www&#46;phpbb&#46;com/community/memberlist&#46;php?mode=group&amp;g=7331" class="postlink"&gt;phpBB MOD Team&lt;/a&gt; will show up. This is &lt;span style="font-weight: bold"&gt;your&lt;/span&gt; chance to speak up to ask your own questions, give us feedback, discuss your concerns, and talk about the future of MODding! Constructive criticism is welcome.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In order to have structure during this convention, we will have specific slots during the day in which each topic will be discussed. It is not mandatory that you ask questions during the exact specified time slots, though it will help facilitate discussion. There are two 2-hour time slots for each topic, in order to accommodate participants in different timezones. You can use &lt;a href="http&#58;//www&#46;timeanddate&#46;com" class="postlink"&gt;TimeAndDate.com&lt;/a&gt; in order to calculate your local time from these given times. Here are the time slots.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: bold"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 150%; line-height: 116%;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #DD6900"&gt;Discussion Topics Time Slots&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: bold"&gt;0:00 to 2:00 UTC, 6:00 to 8:00 UTC&lt;/span&gt;: MODX&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: bold"&gt;2:00 to 4:00 UTC, 12:00 to 14:00 UTC&lt;/span&gt;: Writing MODs for phpBB3&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: bold"&gt;4:00 to 6:00 UTC, 14:00 to 16:00 UTC&lt;/span&gt;: Getting to know phpBB3's inner workings for MODding&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: bold"&gt;8:00 to 10:00 UTC, 18:00 to 20:00 UTC&lt;/span&gt; phpBB &lt;a href="http&#58;//www&#46;phpbb&#46;com/mods/db/" class="postlink"&gt;MODs Database&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: bold"&gt;10:00 to 12:00 UTC, 16:00 to 18:00 UTC&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;a href="http&#58;//www&#46;phpbb&#46;com/mods/documentation/" class="postlink"&gt;phpBB MODding Documentation&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: bold"&gt;20:00 to 24:00 UTC&lt;/span&gt;: Open MODding Discussion&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: bold"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 150%; line-height: 116%;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #DD6900"&gt;Summary&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: bold"&gt;What&lt;/span&gt;: MOD Authors Convention&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: bold"&gt;Who&lt;/span&gt;: You! And the phpBB MOD Team.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: bold"&gt;When&lt;/span&gt;: all day on June 30, 2007&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: bold"&gt;Where&lt;/span&gt;: phpBB MOD IRC channel (&lt;a href="irc&#58;//chat&#46;freenode&#46;net/phpbb-mod" class="postlink"&gt;#phpbb-mod on chat.freenode.net&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: bold"&gt;Topics&lt;/span&gt;: phpBB3 code, phpBB3 MODding, MODX, new phpBB MODDB, MOD Documentation, etc.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You may use &lt;a href="http&#58;//java&#46;freenode&#46;net//index&#46;php?channel=phpbb-mod" class="postlink"&gt;this Java applet&lt;/a&gt; provided by Freenode if you do not wish to install an IRC client. Go &lt;a href="http&#58;//www&#46;wikipedia&#46;org/wiki/Internet_Relay_Chat" class="postlink"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; if you would like to learn more about IRC.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We look forward to seeing you there! &lt;img src="http://www.phpbb.com/community/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":-)" title="Smile" /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The phpBB MOD Team</description>
